---
title: Confetti Burst
description: CSS confetti animation using `transform`, `@keyframes`, and `nth-child` for staggered timing.
slug: confetti
cssFile: confetti.css
explanation: "Each confetti piece is an absolutely-positioned `<div>` with a unique color. The `@keyframes` animation moves pieces from `top: -10px` to below the container using `translateY`, adding rotation and horizontal scale flipping for a tumbling effect. `nth-child` selectors assign different `animation-duration` and `animation-delay` values to each piece so they fall at varied speeds and start times, making it feel organic."
---
{% extends "example.njk" %}
{% block demo %}
<div class="confetti-stage">
	<div class="piece"></div>
	<div class="piece"></div>
	<div class="piece"></div>
	<div class="piece"></div>
	<div class="piece"></div>
	<div class="piece"></div>
	<div class="piece"></div>
	<div class="piece"></div>
	<div class="piece"></div>
	<div class="piece"></div>
	<div class="piece"></div>
	<div class="piece"></div>
	<p class="confetti-text">🎉 Congrats!</p>
</div>
{% endblock %}

{% block html_code %}
{%- highlight "html" %}
<div class="confetti-stage">
  <div class="piece"></div>
  <div class="piece"></div>
  <!-- repeat for more pieces -->
</div>
{%- endhighlight %}
{% endblock %}

{% block css_code %}
{%- highlight "css" %}
.piece {
  position: absolute;
  top: -10px;
  width: 10px;
  height: 10px;
  animation: confetti-fall 3s ease-in infinite;
}

.piece:nth-child(1) { left: 5%; background: var(--coral); animation-delay: 0s; }
.piece:nth-child(2) { left: 20%; background: var(--accent); animation-delay: .3s; }
/* ...more pieces */

@keyframes confetti-fall {
  0%   { transform: translateY(0) rotate(0deg); opacity: 1; }
  100% { transform: translateY(230px) rotate(360deg); opacity: 0; }
}
{%- endhighlight %}
{% endblock %}
